Once upon a time, a God had a little daughter. The daughter liked to explore the planets on his father's cosmos. Suddenly the daughter got sick and died like a collapsing star. God gets alone, angry, depressed and finally mad. He turned all the universe to ash and mixed the ash of her daughter's soul with it to make her alive, But he failed. In the end, he decided to destroy himself to make a New cosmos of all generative planets from ash of himself and his daughter's soul to one more time in the eternity they can be with each other in a heart of a planet. If you listen carefully to the planets, you may hear them calling each other.

metadata.name: Chaos Culture #307
metadata.description:
"Chaos Culture" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022.

„ÄäË•øÈÅäË®ò„ÄãÁ¨¨‰∏ÄÂõû:„ÄåÊ∑∑Ê≤åÊú™ÂàÜÂ§©Âú∞‰∫ÇÔºåËå´Ëå´Ê∏∫Ê∏∫ÁÑ°‰∫∫Ë¶ã„ÄÇ„Äç

Chaos Culture is the final chapter of this series. There is a legend in the East that before Pan Gu opened up the sky and created the earth, the world was a chaotic place, and no one knew its appearance. And I have always been fascinated by this mythical story since he was a child.

These three works have a father-son relationship, Research > Memory > Culture, with each work re-growing through the remnants of the previous work, depending on its image. From the beginning of the creative coding, I like the concept of recursion the most. Here I experiment with my central thinking through this iterative relationship so that the work is not only the shadow of the artist but also the pulling force of repetition.

"Ê∑∑Ê≤å" Chaos in Eastern culture represents the initial state of things. This state is consistent with what we believe in generative art: Anything can happen if different forces are applied. Letting chaos grow out of order and then destroying it, the iterative process, is like my usual dialogue with myself, and maybe it's all just a diary.

Through these three series of works, whether I can eventually find everything in my childhood fantasy, I am not sure yet. The only thing I can be sure of is that I will continue to explore.

- Click the mouse to save an artwork.
- Collectors who own this NFT have the right to print the work.

Artist: Aluan Wang (ileivoivm).
Made with p5js and glsl.

metadata.name: Happy #78
metadata.description:
Impressions of happiness, generated with code.  Press [P] to animate/pause.

Paint strokes are generated in 3D using three.js. You can drag the mouse to explore different views of the same painting. Interactions require a GPU.
Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view.
[P] Play / Pause animation.
[F] Fill the screen.
[1] Save 9:16 image, 3375 x 6000px.
[2] Save 3:4 image, 3000 x 4000px.
[3] Save 1:1 square image, 4000 x 4000px. 
[4] Save 16:9 image, 6000 x 3375px.

Elsif, 2022.04

metadata.name: Kinetograms #378
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.

metadata.name: Botanical Gardens #39
metadata.description:
Question shouldn't be, What is Art?
Just because the answer is quite simple, imagination and creation to inspire.
The question should be, What is Art without dimensions, colors, shades, inspiration, creativity, vibrancy, variations, etc... "NOTHING", we get above all from God's Creation(Art) and no man can ever be a bigger artist than God. 

I always had attraction towards the flowers, the colors, the creativity, the fragrance, all have enticed me to appreciate what we are blessed with.

Botanical Gardens is all about dimensions, colors, vibrancy, and variations.
In this project we go deep with sin & cos to generate patterns of flowers, in comes the Botany's premium color themes range which cover from fade to vibrant colors. Add with some onclick variations, you can always find the best possible locations for your flowers and save.

This project is token of my appreciation to God for blessing us all, with this amazing art surrounding us.

Click on NFT to see the flower dance.
Press "S" to save 1000x1000 png of your mint.
You are welcome to request a Hi-Res image for your holdings via twitter @TheRealBotany

metadata.name: Tangled #169
metadata.description:
"Tangled" is a generative art project that explores the emergent behaviour of simple shapes moving according to a random flow field. While the final result is always constrained to the shape of a circle, the variation within is endless.

Instructions:
Press "p" to pause the animation.
In live mode, press 1 through 5 to save a PNG version of the final result. The following resolutions are available:
1: 400 x 400 (ideal for Twitter PFP)
2: 1000 x 1000
3: 2000 x 2000
4: 4000 x 4000
5: 5000 x 5000
Please be patient, generating the PNG may take some time!

Made with p5.js.
